President Obama congratulates U Htin Kyaw on his inauguration as president of Burma and expresses his anticipation of working with him and the new government. The president views this inauguration as a significant milestone in Burma's transition to a democratically elected, civilian-led government. He commends the people, institutions, and leaders of Burma for their efforts in ensuring a peaceful transfer of power and acknowledges the reforms the country has undertaken since 2011. President Obama recognizes that Burma will face challenges moving forward, such as achieving economic development, national reconciliation, and promoting the rights and freedoms of its people. The United States aims to be a friend and partner to the new government and the people of Burma as they strive towards a more inclusive, peaceful, and prosperous future.